entries.name: FastExternalBridge
entries.description: A Facet implementation of the ETH Bridge. This bridge is also called "fast bridge" as it uses a permissioned EOA as operator for faster withdrawal processing.

entries.name: FacetSafeModule
entries.description: Module that allows the Safe to send Facet transactions.

entries.name: L1Bridge
entries.description: L1Bridge is an ETH bridge built on top of Rollup contract. It is the selected canonical bridge for this risk analysis. It used to bridge ETH from L1 to L2. Note that the token received on L2 has a different ticker/symbol than the token sent on L1.

entries.name: Rollup
entries.description: Rollup contract for Facet. This is the core contract that manages the state of the rollup and its proof system.

entries.name: SP1VerifierGateway
entries.description: This contract is the router for zk proof verification. It stores the mapping between identifiers and the address of onchain verifier contracts, routing each identifier to the corresponding verifier contract.

activeVerifiers.description: Verifiers that are routed to by their selector and not frozen.

allVerifiers.description: All verifiers that were ever routed to by this gateway.

entries.name: L1ETHLockbox
entries.description: Deprecated entry point to deposit ERC20 tokens from host chain to this chain. Currently just holds ETH that the Facet multisig can withdraw.

entries.name: FacetSafeProxy
entries.description: Helper of the Safe Module that allows to send Facet transactions.
